- "years of seasoned experience" refers to more than three years of experience.

- The "roots" of the company structure refer to the top-level employees who have no manager;
- The "branches" refer to the lower-level employees who are managed by others;
- The "blossoms" metaphorically represent the different levels of the employee hierarchy.

